# Day 1 - Networking Basics

Today I learned the basics of networking from TryHackMe.
---

 What I Learned

 Networking
Networking means connecting devices together so they can communicate and share data.

---

 IP Address
An IP address is a unique address assigned to a device. It is used to send data to the correct device on a network.

---

MAC Address
A MAC address is a unique hardware identifier for a device’s network interface. It is assigned by the manufacturer and can be spoofed (faked) in some cases.

---

 Ping
Ping is a tool used to test connectivity between devices. It uses ICMP (Internet Control Message Protocol) to check if a device is reachable.

---

 My Understanding (in simple words)
I understood that networking is about communication between devices, and each device has an identity like IP and MAC addresses.

---

Key Takeaway
Even basic networking concepts are very important in cybersecurity because they help us understand how devices communicate and how attacks can happen.
